HEADWORD: Zonar
<hw>Zo"nar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Mod. Gr. <?/ a girdle,
fr. Gr. <?/, dim. of <?/ a girdle. See <er>Zone</er>.]</ety> <def>A belt
or girdle which the Christians and Jews of the Levant were obliged to
wear to distinguish them from Mohammedans.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>zonnar</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

